  "instructions": [
    {
      "step": 1,
      "text": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> and chop your <strong>leek[s] </strong>in half lengthways, wash thoroughly then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1454.-step-1-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 2,
      "text": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a large knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> and <strong>sliced leek </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until softened</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1454.-step-2-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 3,
      "text": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1454.-step-3-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 4,
      "text": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 550ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[775ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>– this is your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>vegetable stock</strong></p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1454.-step-4-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 5,
      "text": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Add the<strong> creamy vegetable stock </strong>and <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> and cook for 15-18 min or until the potatoes are almost fork-tender</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1454.-step-5-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 6,
      "text": "<p>Once the potatoes<strong> </strong>are almost fork-tender, add your <strong>diced pollock</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong> to the pot and cook for 4-5 min or until the pollock is cooked through and the potatoes are fork-tender</p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized diced pollock? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!</p><p>Season to taste with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1454.-step-6-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 7,
      "text": "<p>While the pollock and potatoes are cooking, chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Once everything is done, add the <strong>grated cheese</strong> to the pot and gently stir everything together – this is your<strong> one pot cheesy pollock & leek chowder</strong></p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1454.-step-7-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 8,
      "text": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pot cheesy pollock & leek chowder</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped chives</strong> and season with a good grind of<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>"
    }
  ],
